I went to this location, hoping to get a nice meal after work and when I first went inside I could tell that nobody wanted me there. I got side eyes from the employees, it looked like they were about to close which is reasonable because I work at a food place as well so I understand how it can be when a customer walks in last minute but this was out of hand. There was light skin girl that did my bowl, I asked her to put extra sour cream and extra chicken, when she added the chicken she seemed like she did not want to add the extra chicken that I had asked for. She repeatedly asked me if I wanted “ extra chicken “ and I repeatedly told her that I did. Even after repeatedly saying the same thing she did not add the extra chicken, the manager came out to try and figure out what was going on but did not take any action towards the problem. The same girl from before was finishing it up and then added wayyy too much sour cream to the point where the top could not close without the cream spilling off all the sides of the bowl. At this point I’m frustrated with both the manager and the employee and I take my food and leave because I asked for something simple and the service I got was more than ridiculous. I will never go back to this chipotle ever again, and they need a new set of employees that are there for the customers.
